info.headline: Flood Advisory issued July 15 at 9:42PM CDT until July 15 at 10:45PM CDT by NWS Duluth MN
info.description:
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.
* WHERE...In Minnesota, Carlton and St. Louis Counties and Wisconsin, Douglas County.
* WHEN...Until 1045 PM CDT Tuesday.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. Overflowing poor drainage areas. Ponding of water in urban or other areas is occurring or is imminent.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 942 PM CDT Tuesday, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Minor flooding is already occurring in Cloquet. Between 0.75 and 3.5 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts up to 0.5 inches are expected over the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Duluth, Superior, Cloquet, Hermantown, Proctor, Moose Lake, Scanlon, Carlton, Mahtowa, Barnum, Wrenshall, Oliver, Cromwell, Kettle River, Thomson, Fond Du Lac Band Cloquet Area, Jay Cooke State Park, Fond Du Lac Band Sawyer Area, Fond Du Lac Band Brookston Area and Pike Lake Near Duluth. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood.
info.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding.
Report observed flooding to local emergency services or law enforcement and to the National Weather Service in Duluth when you can do so safely. Flooding can be reported to the National Weather Service at 1-800-685-8612.
